.TH TGLFS-UPLOAD 1 "March 2026" "tglfs 0.1.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tglfs-upload \- upload one file, or archive multiple files, into Telegram Saved Messages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tglfs upload
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIpaths...\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Uploads one file directly into Saved Messages, or packages multiple files into a tar archive using the same naming convention as the web app before uploading.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --no-interactive
Disable interactive prompts and fail instead of prompting.
.TP
.B --password <password>
Encryption password.
.TP
.B --password-env [name]
Read the encryption password from an environment variable. If no name is provided, the command uses
.B TGLFS_UPLOAD_PASSWORD.
.TP
.B --password-stdin
Read the encryption password from standard input.
.TP
.B --json
Emit machine-readable JSON.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B TGLFS_UPLOAD_PASSWORD
Default environment variable for the upload encryption password.
.SH AI AGENT NOTES
TTY uploads render separate UFID and upload progress bars.
.B --json
prints exactly one final JSON object to standard output, writes failures to standard error, and never prompts. If no password flag, environment variable, or stdin source is supplied, uploads default to no encryption.
